{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3da9fb37-59ac-4de7-a9d1-0111132444b2","content":"If you need per-test setup logging, move it to `[TestInitialize]` where `TestContext.TestName` is valid:\n\n```csharp\n[TestInitialize]\npublic void TestInit()\n{\n    var testName = TestContext.TestName;\n    // Log setup for specific test\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Other v4 changes to watch for\n\n| Area | What changed |\n|---|---|\n| **Package** | Single `MSTest` package replaces the old `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` + `MSTest.Analyzers` trio |\n| **`Assert.AreEqual` on doubles** | Now uses exact comparison by default; pass an explicit delta if you relied on tolerance |\n| **`[DataRow]` type coercion** | Stricter type matching — `[DataRow(1)]` won't auto-coerce to `long` parameter |\n| **`[ClassCleanup]` timing** | Defaults to `EndOfClass` (was `EndOfAssembly`); change with `[ClassCleanup(ClassCleanupBehavior.EndOfAssembly)]` if needed |\n| **Parallelization** | Class-level parallelism is enabled by default; add `[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]` or disable if tests share state |\n| **`TestContext.WriteLine`** | Throws if called after test completes (e.g., in async continuations) |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"267975e9-9568-4567-9542-61560d0056ea","outputTokens":354,"requestId":"67C5:1F50C6:1CB65E7:2058486:69FD5464"},"id":"86912ac6-558f-4a3e-bead-f950d69068b5","timestamp":"2026-05-08T03:11:40.714Z","parentId":"523560b0-d6fe-4019-8ae0-cc3137a96ffb"}
